 GONK /gonk/ vt.,n. 1. To prevaricate or to embellish the truth beyond any
reasonable recognition. In German the term is (fictively) "GONKEN", in
spanish the verb becomes "GONKAR." "You're gonking me. That story you just
told me is a bunch of gonk." In German, "Du Gonkst mir." (You're pulling my
leg.) see also GONKULATOR. 2. [British] To grab some sleep at an odd time.